column5: If I have an Ontario license and a Minnesota license, am I allowed to have 10 walleyes in my freezer in Minnesota?
I don't believe so. Because there is no way to tell if you actually caught them in MN.
I believe you can, but only if you stop at the US customs on the way out of Canada and have your fish stamped that they were caught in Canada.
They will know now. with the full resources of the goverment at their fingertips they just might. hurry and eat them before its too late, they could be on their way now. dont answer the door!
